Module mesakit.graph.world
Package com.telenav.mesakit.graph.world.grid

Class WorldGrid

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.world.grid.WorldGrid
public class WorldGrid extends Object
A grid of WorldCells, each containing its own cell-Graph. The grid is stored in a WorldGraphRepository inside a WorldGraphRepositoryFolder and it consists of a WorldGraphIndex stored in a file called "index.world" and a set of cell graphs, each named according to its index in the world grid. For example, the graph file for the cell at grid coordinate (60, 36) would be called "cell-60-36.graph".

Attributes

  • worldGraph() - The world graph that owns this grid
  • name() - The name of this grid from the repository folder
  • mode() - The WorldGraph.AccessMode for this grid
  • metadata() - Metadata describing the entire grid
  • grid() - The grid layout for this grid

Repositories

  • repositoryFolder() - The repository folder holding this grid

Cells

  • cells() - All cells in this grid
  • worldCell(WorldCell.WorldCellIdentifier) - The cell in this grid with the given identifier
  • worldCell(int) - The cell for the identifier
  • worldCell(String) - The cell with the given name
  • worldCell(GridCell) - The cell for the given grid cell
  • worldCell(Location) - The cell containing the given location
  • neighbors(Location) - Cells within one meter of the given location
  • included() - The world cells included in this grid
  • included(WorldCell) - True if the given cell is in this grid

Indexing

  • index() - The WorldGraphIndex for this grid
  • saveIndex(WorldGraphRepositoryFolder, Metadata) - Saves the index for this grid to the given repository folder with the given metadata
